Job Description

The project's goal is to integrate the global engineering and product team of a large group in the telco area, where we develop OTT and streaming and video apps for the USA, Europe, and Africa. The main product is highly complex streaming platforms with over 50 million users. You will join the metadata team. The goal is to work on an internal consumption app. The app already exists but needs to be redone – setting up the framework, pipelines, and starting feature development. You will have the opportunity to help define the technology used and partly develop the project from scratch. We are looking for someone who is autonomous, has critical thinking skills, and is capable of researching and exploring.


Qualifications


Degree in the field;
Between 3 and 10 years' experience;
Comfortable developing with Kotlin;
Experience with TypeScript and React;
Experience with Python;
Knowledge of CI/CD, as well as tools such as Jenkins and Kubernetes;
Contact with AWS;
Proficiency in English, minimum level C1;
We are looking for someone who is autonomous, has critical thinking skills and is capable of researching and exploring. 


Additional Information

